WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:17.330 --> 00:00:20.540
Did you know there's an awesome treasure at the end of this sea?!

3
00:00:20.540 --> 00:00:23.340
And whoever gets it becomes King of the Pirates!

4
00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:24.960
Isn't that exciting?!

5
00:00:24.960 --> 00:00:28.010
Cool new adventures are waiting out there!

6
00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:38.060
BON VOYAGE! Light the ember of courage and let the fire grow

7
00:00:38.060 --> 00:00:45.660
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

8
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:48.210
Back when we first started

9
00:00:48.210 --> 00:00:53.430
we had separate ideas about where we would soon go

10
00:00:53.740 --> 00:00:55.380
Things have changed now,

11
00:00:55.380 --> 00:01:00.440
when we look towards our dreams we all share one telescope

12
00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:05.680
When you find that your heart's been led astray

13
00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:09.980
time to calibrate your compasses

14
00:01:09.980 --> 00:01:13.010
Set a new course, turn the tables now

15
00:01:13.010 --> 00:01:20.300
BON VOYAGE! Shed your previous baggage, forget the past

16
00:01:20.300 --> 00:01:27.140
Smiles can weather a storm, we know that better than anyone

17
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:29.080
Don't you fret,

18
00:01:29.080 --> 00:01:34.900
tears shed along the way to your dreams are not in vain

19
00:01:34.900 --> 00:01:41.100
You know that you're all PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE

20
00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:49.210
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

21
00:01:52.380 --> 00:01:54.340
I-It's a snake!

22
00:01:54.720 --> 00:01:55.800
Could this be...?

23
00:01:56.180 --> 00:01:58.430
Hey, Kalgara! Look at this!

24
00:02:00.060 --> 00:02:04.020
What a surprise! That snake
must have had a grandchild.

25
00:02:04.650 --> 00:02:06.440
"That snake"?

26
00:02:08.520 --> 00:02:09.610
Snake, huh?

27
00:02:13.860 --> 00:02:16.950
I don't get those two...

28
00:02:16.950 --> 00:02:20.040
They were trying to kill each other
until just recently...

29
00:02:20.040 --> 00:02:22.540
but now, they're
practically inseparable!

30
00:02:22.540 --> 00:02:26.250
Kalgara's not even that friendly
with his fellow villagers.

31
00:02:27.250 --> 00:02:29.750
I've never seen him smile
like this before...

32
00:02:31.960 --> 00:02:33.970
Just follow me.

33
00:02:35.130 --> 00:02:36.970
We'll climb down through here.

34
00:02:36.970 --> 00:02:38.470
Climb down?

35
00:02:39.430 --> 00:02:43.690
<b>The Light of Shandora</b>

36
00:02:49.690 --> 00:02:51.530
This ringing...

37
00:02:52.530 --> 00:02:55.780
Hey, Kalgara! Where is this
beautiful ringing coming from?!

38
00:02:55.780 --> 00:02:58.740
Follow me and you'll see.

39
00:03:36.450 --> 00:03:38.030
They're here!

40
00:03:38.030 --> 00:03:40.030
Lost for words?

41
00:03:40.030 --> 00:03:41.870
This is Shandora, the City of Gold.

42
00:03:41.870 --> 00:03:44.910
We are what remains of its people.

43
00:03:45.370 --> 00:03:47.370
A city of gold...

44
00:03:47.920 --> 00:03:50.880
It's like I'm dreaming!

45
00:03:51.290 --> 00:03:54.510
Wh-Whoa! It's all gold!

46
00:03:54.510 --> 00:03:58.180
It's a city of treasure!

47
00:03:58.180 --> 00:04:01.220
H-Hey, guys! Come on!

48
00:04:01.890 --> 00:04:03.220
It's fine.

49
00:04:03.220 --> 00:04:08.100
Load your ship with all the treasure
you want, aside from the golden bell!

50
00:04:10.020 --> 00:04:12.650
We villagers won't
take no for an answer.

51
00:04:12.650 --> 00:04:16.860
We owe you for saving our tribe
from that terrible disease.

52
00:04:17.320 --> 00:04:18.610
It's the least we can do.

53
00:04:19.360 --> 00:04:21.240
You're so generous, Great Warrior!

54
00:04:21.240 --> 00:04:26.200
But haven't your people been
protecting the city all this time?

55
00:04:26.200 --> 00:04:27.580
Indeed.

56
00:04:27.580 --> 00:04:31.380
We've been protecting the city, but...

57
00:04:31.380 --> 00:04:35.210
to us, the gold holds little value!

58
00:04:35.670 --> 00:04:38.090
To be more specific...

59
00:04:45.520 --> 00:04:47.520
we were protecting this stone.

60
00:04:49.230 --> 00:04:51.900
What is this?

61
00:04:51.900 --> 00:04:53.310
Writing?

62
00:04:53.310 --> 00:04:54.940
A historical record.

63
00:04:54.940 --> 00:04:57.690
It's known as a poneglyph.

64
00:04:57.690 --> 00:05:00.070
Even we are unable to read it.

65
00:05:00.070 --> 00:05:04.240
You mean this wasn't written
by your ancestors?

66
00:05:04.740 --> 00:05:06.870
We know one thing for certain:

67
00:05:06.870 --> 00:05:12.830
Shandora fell during a desperate
battle to protect this stone.

68
00:05:13.170 --> 00:05:17.420
We must continue to protect it
with the same resolve.

69
00:05:17.420 --> 00:05:19.010
As their descendants,

70
00:05:19.010 --> 00:05:23.340
we must protect the legacy for which
our ancestors risked their lives.

71
00:05:23.800 --> 00:05:27.810
We revere our forefathers
as we would gods.

72
00:05:27.810 --> 00:05:33.860
Who would've thought it was the ringing
of such a massive golden bell...

73
00:05:35.770 --> 00:05:38.690
That ringing carries a message.

74
00:05:38.690 --> 00:05:40.110
A message?

75
00:05:40.110 --> 00:05:44.030
It's for our ancestors who
were greeted by the heavens.

76
00:05:44.030 --> 00:05:49.120
So that they may always be guided
back home to this land,

77
00:05:49.120 --> 00:05:52.670
we continue to ring this bell,
as a way to say:

78
00:05:52.670 --> 00:05:56.090
"We are here."

79
00:05:57.210 --> 00:06:02.510
Its sound proclaims the undeniable
glory of Shandora's past,

80
00:06:02.510 --> 00:06:06.100
and makes its existence known
to the ends of the sea!

81
00:06:06.100 --> 00:06:09.220
We will never run or hide!

82
00:06:10.100 --> 00:06:14.940
That is why we call this city's
grand bell the "Light of Shandora."

83
00:06:15.480 --> 00:06:18.980
A fitting name to match
its majestic sound.

84
00:06:18.980 --> 00:06:20.360
Do you think so?!

85
00:06:20.360 --> 00:06:21.440
Yes!

86
00:06:22.030 --> 00:06:26.660
That day, the light embraced us
and guided us here.

87
00:06:28.490 --> 00:06:35.120
In the middle of a deafening storm,
I heard the ringing of this very bell.

88
00:06:39.710 --> 00:06:43.340
You like the sound
of this bell too, huh?

89
00:06:43.340 --> 00:06:47.890
I wonder if you'll become
a giant serpent too someday.

90
00:06:52.810 --> 00:06:55.730
Let's check back
in a hundred years or so!

91
00:06:58.270 --> 00:07:01.480
Hey! Stay here as long
as you like, Noland!

92
00:07:01.980 --> 00:07:07.620
Shandora has had no guests
since its fall 400 years ago!

93
00:07:07.620 --> 00:07:09.700
Let me show you
our finest hospitality!

94
00:07:11.330 --> 00:07:13.080
I appreciate it.

95
00:07:13.080 --> 00:07:15.830
I do want to collect plants
from the forest,

96
00:07:15.830 --> 00:07:18.920
and I'd like to see this plague
through to its end.

97
00:07:18.920 --> 00:07:22.050
Commodore! Commodore!

98
00:07:22.050 --> 00:07:24.050
Whoa now, what's with those outfits?

99
00:07:24.050 --> 00:07:26.090
Look, look! An eternal pose!

100
00:07:26.090 --> 00:07:27.840
And a map, Commodore! A map!

101
00:07:28.890 --> 00:07:32.060
We took these from intruders.

102
00:07:32.600 --> 00:07:33.850
Yeah.

103
00:07:33.850 --> 00:07:36.810
The skull shape is
definitely this island.

104
00:07:36.810 --> 00:07:41.570
The name "Shandora" means
"the skull's right eye,"

105
00:07:41.570 --> 00:07:45.490
which points to this city's location.

106
00:07:47.200 --> 00:07:48.910
Well, take care!

107
00:07:48.910 --> 00:07:51.580
Be sure she gets lots of rest!

108
00:07:51.580 --> 00:07:53.910
Thank you, Doctor!

109
00:07:56.460 --> 00:07:58.290
Hey! Come look, everyone!

110
00:07:58.290 --> 00:08:01.540
Noland said he'll give us
some weird crops!

111
00:08:01.540 --> 00:08:06.590
There's a greenhouse on the ship
with all sorts of plant specimens.

112
00:08:06.590 --> 00:08:09.840
I'll leave some seeds and sprouts
that are suited for your soil.

113
00:08:09.840 --> 00:08:11.850
Does it taste good?

114
00:08:11.850 --> 00:08:14.810
Sure does! And it's rich in nutrients!

115
00:09:15.450 --> 00:09:16.990
All right!

116
00:09:16.990 --> 00:09:18.910
Let's work hard again today!

117
00:09:19.290 --> 00:09:21.330
Work hard doing what?

118
00:09:21.330 --> 00:09:22.960
Having a campfire party?!

119
00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:30.420
<b>One Month After Landfall</b>

120
00:09:31.300 --> 00:09:32.640
Why?!

121
00:09:32.640 --> 00:09:35.350
Why would the doctor
and his friends do this?!

122
00:09:40.060 --> 00:09:43.020
Chief! Noland's crew is coming!

123
00:09:43.900 --> 00:09:47.650
Listen! Do not speak of last night!

124
00:09:47.650 --> 00:09:50.740
They said they're planning
to set sail in a few days.

125
00:09:51.110 --> 00:09:55.030
Make absolutely sure
not to do anything rash!

126
00:09:55.410 --> 00:09:59.290
I knew it... Our peoples can
never see eye to eye!

127
00:09:59.700 --> 00:10:04.380
No matter how good his
medicine is, he's still a godkiller!

128
00:10:04.380 --> 00:10:08.800
Do they think themselves so great
that they can trample all over our history?!

129
00:10:09.590 --> 00:10:14.180
Suppress your feelings
and quietly wait for them to leave!

130
00:10:14.180 --> 00:10:15.510
They're here!

131
00:10:18.470 --> 00:10:19.970
Hey, guys!

132
00:10:19.970 --> 00:10:21.430
Is Kalgara around?

133
00:10:30.320 --> 00:10:34.490
What's with the cold shoulder
all of a sudden? Where's Kalgara?

134
00:10:34.490 --> 00:10:37.870
You guys are still outsiders!

135
00:10:37.870 --> 00:10:41.370
Kalgara said he doesn't want
to see you anymore!

136
00:10:41.370 --> 00:10:42.290
Seto!

137
00:10:45.120 --> 00:10:48.420
Just when are you all
going to leave, anyway?

138
00:10:48.790 --> 00:10:49.630
Huh?!

139
00:10:50.710 --> 00:10:55.220
They seem to hate us
all of a sudden...

140
00:10:55.220 --> 00:10:59.470
Hey, what gives?! The way you're
acting doesn't make sense!

141
00:10:59.470 --> 00:11:00.470
Stop.

142
00:11:02.680 --> 00:11:05.640
Let's just keep working.

143
00:11:06.350 --> 00:11:09.060
We're not done inspecting the forest.

144
00:11:12.110 --> 00:11:14.150
There you are, Kalgara!

145
00:11:14.150 --> 00:11:15.860
Noland was looking for you!

146
00:11:15.860 --> 00:11:19.410
Yeah. I don't want
to see his face again.

147
00:11:19.990 --> 00:11:24.500
If I do, I might just kill him!

148
00:11:30.880 --> 00:11:33.380
The bell didn't ring today...

149
00:11:33.380 --> 00:11:34.260
Yeah.

150
00:11:34.260 --> 00:11:38.220
That hasn't happened in the month
we've been here, has it?

151
00:11:38.890 --> 00:11:40.300
Commodore...

152
00:11:40.300 --> 00:11:43.470
We'll be finished inspecting
the forest in two days.

153
00:11:43.470 --> 00:11:44.930
Y-Yes, sir...

154
00:11:45.560 --> 00:11:50.440
Tell the crew we set sail
again in three days,

155
00:11:50.440 --> 00:11:54.150
so make sure to enjoy
the solid ground while we can.

156
00:11:54.740 --> 00:11:59.110
Commodore, to be honest, it doesn't
feel right to stay here any longer...

157
00:11:59.110 --> 00:12:01.530
We have to finish what we started!

158
00:12:01.530 --> 00:12:02.530
Rest up.

159
00:12:04.910 --> 00:12:07.040
Stay here, Noland!

160
00:12:07.040 --> 00:12:11.040
Oh! Why not take
Mousse as your wife?

161
00:12:11.040 --> 00:12:12.210
Don't be silly!

162
00:12:12.210 --> 00:12:15.420
I have a family back home,
including a child about her age.

163
00:12:15.420 --> 00:12:16.550
I have to go back.

164
00:12:16.920 --> 00:12:20.390
Kalgara said he doesn't want
to see you anymore!

165
00:12:21.550 --> 00:12:25.140
Just when are you all
going to leave, anyway?

166
00:12:30.810 --> 00:12:33.070
I know you're here, Kalgara!

167
00:12:33.070 --> 00:12:34.570
Show yourself!

168
00:12:35.190 --> 00:12:38.200
Don't you think I'm owed
an explanation?!

169
00:12:38.200 --> 00:12:39.820
Out with it!

170
00:12:39.820 --> 00:12:41.780
I'm not a mind reader!

171
00:12:42.410 --> 00:12:45.040
We're setting sail soon!

172
00:12:45.040 --> 00:12:47.620
I don't want to part ways like this!

173
00:13:00.760 --> 00:13:04.180
Don't show your face
around me again!

174
00:13:04.180 --> 00:13:07.470
Or must we part ways
through death?!

175
00:13:11.190 --> 00:13:12.650
Kalgara!

176
00:13:16.730 --> 00:13:19.610
The commodore seems lonely...

177
00:13:19.610 --> 00:13:20.900
Yeah.

178
00:13:20.900 --> 00:13:26.120
And after making such a great friend
so very far from home...

179
00:13:27.790 --> 00:13:30.160
None of this makes any sense!

180
00:13:30.160 --> 00:13:34.170
We set sail first thing
tomorrow morning...

181
00:13:34.170 --> 00:13:37.050
The villagers are so bloodthirsty
we can't go near 'em.

182
00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:41.130
Not to mention, the bell
didn't ring today, either...

183
00:13:43.890 --> 00:13:46.930
Don't show your face
around me again!

184
00:13:46.930 --> 00:13:49.890
Or must we part ways
through death?!

185
00:14:06.160 --> 00:14:11.000
What a heartrending way to leave...

186
00:14:11.000 --> 00:14:11.960
Um...

187
00:14:16.540 --> 00:14:17.630
Doctor...

188
00:14:18.170 --> 00:14:19.670
Mousse?!

189
00:14:19.670 --> 00:14:22.260
Do you have a minute?

190
00:14:26.930 --> 00:14:30.220
What kind of botanist would do this?!

191
00:14:36.150 --> 00:14:37.770
Noland!

192
00:14:38.190 --> 00:14:42.150
If these are the victims
of your so-called "progress,"

193
00:14:42.150 --> 00:14:46.570
then we should never
have accepted you!

194
00:14:49.910 --> 00:14:51.290
Ancestral trees?

195
00:14:52.120 --> 00:14:53.160
Yes.

196
00:14:54.330 --> 00:14:58.630
It's said that the spirits of our
ancestors who died on this island

197
00:14:58.630 --> 00:15:02.340
dwell within them, guided there
by the sound of the bell.

198
00:15:02.340 --> 00:15:06.720
Our ancestors have lived here
since the age of Shandora long ago.

199
00:15:06.720 --> 00:15:13.680
Each one of them watches over us
from those sacred white trees.

200
00:15:20.150 --> 00:15:24.030
To us Shandians,
the ancestral trees are so precious

201
00:15:24.360 --> 00:15:31.870
that we've protected them
as we would our own lives!

202
00:15:31.870 --> 00:15:34.870
And we went and
chopped them all down...

203
00:15:36.250 --> 00:15:40.960
The warriors were so angry
they were immediately up in arms...

204
00:15:40.960 --> 00:15:43.090
Drive them from the island!

205
00:15:43.090 --> 00:15:44.420
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

206
00:15:46.760 --> 00:15:53.140
...but we owed you for saving
so many villagers' lives...

207
00:15:53.140 --> 00:15:55.020
I see.

208
00:15:56.100 --> 00:15:59.100
So they were just
holding back their anger...

209
00:15:59.980 --> 00:16:02.570
Even if it was for your research...

210
00:16:03.320 --> 00:16:04.780
even if you didn't know...

211
00:16:05.490 --> 00:16:09.110
the village's anger will never subside.

212
00:16:09.110 --> 00:16:12.280
So, I thought I would at least
ask before you left...

213
00:16:14.500 --> 00:16:16.710
Why did you do it?

214
00:16:18.830 --> 00:16:20.580
Hey! Someone help with this!

215
00:16:19.960 --> 00:16:23.170
Trees where the spirits
of their ancestors dwell...

216
00:16:20.580 --> 00:16:21.960
Get it all on board now!

217
00:16:21.960 --> 00:16:24.550
Make sure to tie them up properly!

218
00:16:23.170 --> 00:16:25.340
I had no idea.

219
00:16:25.340 --> 00:16:28.180
We can never take back
what we've done here.

220
00:16:28.550 --> 00:16:31.010
The villagers are right to be angry.

221
00:16:31.010 --> 00:16:32.140
But, Commodore!

222
00:16:32.140 --> 00:16:33.220
We had no choice, given–

223
00:16:33.220 --> 00:16:35.140
There's no excusing it!

224
00:16:35.890 --> 00:16:38.980
I only cared to satisfy
my own conscience...

225
00:16:39.560 --> 00:16:41.690
I was told...

226
00:16:41.690 --> 00:16:44.940
that aside from proclaiming
the city's existence,

227
00:16:44.940 --> 00:16:49.200
that bell also served to guide the
spirits of their ancestors back to the island.

228
00:16:49.820 --> 00:16:54.620
And we cut down the very
trees that housed them!

229
00:16:55.120 --> 00:16:57.040
They have no reason to forgive us!

230
00:16:57.620 --> 00:17:00.080
Commodore...

231
00:17:02.460 --> 00:17:04.420
Listen up, everyone!

232
00:17:04.420 --> 00:17:06.260
– Huh?!
– Huh?!

233
00:17:06.260 --> 00:17:09.220
– You want us to leave all the gold?!
– You want us to leave all the gold?!

234
00:17:10.720 --> 00:17:14.140
Noland and his men
are preparing to set sail.

235
00:17:24.610 --> 00:17:27.230
Mousse! Where were you?!

236
00:17:29.780 --> 00:17:30.740
What if...

237
00:17:31.610 --> 00:17:35.200
What if you knew that
a single, precious tree...

238
00:17:35.700 --> 00:17:38.160
was tainted with a deadly poison...

239
00:17:38.910 --> 00:17:42.830
and that this poison would eventually
spread throughout the forest,

240
00:17:43.330 --> 00:17:46.300
then to its people,
killing the entire island?

241
00:17:46.300 --> 00:17:49.050
What if you knew beforehand?!

242
00:17:49.340 --> 00:17:50.920
What are you saying?

243
00:17:50.920 --> 00:17:52.380
What are you talking about?!

244
00:17:52.380 --> 00:17:54.050
If it was us...

245
00:17:55.430 --> 00:17:57.760
what would we do...

246
00:17:59.560 --> 00:18:01.440
with that single, precious tree?!

247
00:18:03.560 --> 00:18:06.820
Papa, hurry and stop them!

248
00:18:06.820 --> 00:18:09.690
Don't be a fool!
You know what they've done!

249
00:18:09.690 --> 00:18:13.030
If we leave things like this,
we'll regret it for the rest of our lives!

250
00:18:13.030 --> 00:18:15.990
You finally made such a dear friend,

251
00:18:15.990 --> 00:18:18.450
and we Shandians owe them so much!

252
00:18:18.450 --> 00:18:20.910
Let them go, and their pain
will never heal!

253
00:18:21.410 --> 00:18:23.120
What are you talking about?!

254
00:18:23.750 --> 00:18:25.790
It'll probably sound like an excuse...

255
00:18:26.380 --> 00:18:30.210
but for the commodore's honor,
I'll tell you anyway.

256
00:18:30.210 --> 00:18:33.470
Those woods of yours
were already dead.

257
00:18:33.470 --> 00:18:34.470
Huh?!

258
00:18:35.090 --> 00:18:37.930
The true horror of a
tree fever outbreak...

259
00:18:38.560 --> 00:18:42.390
is that it also infects plant life.

260
00:18:43.020 --> 00:18:45.230
It was because he knew this

261
00:18:45.230 --> 00:18:48.980
that the commodore risked
his own life to plead with you.

262
00:18:50.360 --> 00:18:53.150
From people to forest,
from forest to people...

263
00:18:53.150 --> 00:18:58.410
That is precisely how it
devastates small islands.

264
00:19:00.410 --> 00:19:02.790
But there's nothing
to worry about now.

265
00:19:02.790 --> 00:19:06.710
We finished checking
the entire forest yesterday.

266
00:19:06.710 --> 00:19:09.880
I'm sorry, we had no idea
the trees we cut down were precious,

267
00:19:09.880 --> 00:19:11.960
but we still should have explained.

268
00:19:12.460 --> 00:19:16.090
Well, I don't expect you to forgive us,
even with an explanation...

269
00:19:16.090 --> 00:19:20.470
but a botanist would never harm
a forest without good reason.

270
00:19:20.930 --> 00:19:24.690
It's not that the commodore
hates gods or spirits...

271
00:19:28.900 --> 00:19:31.860
it's just that he always knows...

272
00:19:31.860 --> 00:19:33.610
what's most important.

273
00:19:34.820 --> 00:19:38.870
That means... they did it for us?

274
00:19:43.950 --> 00:19:44.960
Papa!

275
00:19:47.620 --> 00:19:49.420
I'm sorry, Noland!

276
00:19:50.040 --> 00:19:52.170
Don't go yet!

277
00:19:53.050 --> 00:19:54.880
Everyone have everything?

278
00:19:55.760 --> 00:19:57.340
Not everything...

279
00:19:57.340 --> 00:19:59.340
Quit mopin'! Forget about it!

280
00:19:59.850 --> 00:20:01.430
Alright! It's time to go!

281
00:20:01.430 --> 00:20:02.890
Positions, everyone!

282
00:20:02.890 --> 00:20:05.810
We're heading home to
the Kingdom of Lvneel!

283
00:20:05.810 --> 00:20:08.150
– Aye, aye!
– Aye, aye!

284
00:20:08.150 --> 00:20:10.610
Noland!

285
00:20:11.310 --> 00:20:13.980
I've committed a grave sin!

286
00:20:13.980 --> 00:20:17.570
Wait! Noland!

287
00:20:19.530 --> 00:20:22.240
Set sail!

288
00:20:30.210 --> 00:20:31.500
Why...

289
00:20:32.340 --> 00:20:33.920
is the bell ringing?

290
00:20:34.840 --> 00:20:36.800
Ring it!

291
00:20:37.130 --> 00:20:39.590
We're sorry, Noland!

292
00:20:39.590 --> 00:20:41.140
Louder!

293
00:20:41.140 --> 00:20:43.140
Make sure Noland's crew can hear it!

294
00:20:46.220 --> 00:20:47.560
Commodore! Look!

295
00:20:57.360 --> 00:21:01.030
Noland!

296
00:21:01.450 --> 00:21:03.240
Kalgara...

297
00:21:17.840 --> 00:21:22.930
Come back again!

298
00:21:24.050 --> 00:21:25.890
Noland...

299
00:21:25.890 --> 00:21:29.350
I'll be waiting right here for you!

300
00:21:30.520 --> 00:21:33.560
I'll keep ringing the bell for you!

301
00:21:33.980 --> 00:21:38.990
So that your ship won't get
lost at sea when you return...

302
00:21:38.990 --> 00:21:42.990
So that you won't lose sight
of this island during a storm...

303
00:21:42.990 --> 00:21:47.330
I'll ring the bell and wait for you!

304
00:21:56.630 --> 00:22:02.760
Let's make sure to meet again
someday... my precious friend!

305
00:22:05.220 --> 00:22:06.510
I can...

306
00:22:07.220 --> 00:22:09.720
come back again?

307
00:22:12.940 --> 00:22:15.520
Of course I'll come back!

308
00:22:15.520 --> 00:22:17.070
I will!

309
00:22:20.860 --> 00:22:25.660
Let's meet again someday for sure!

310
00:22:34.980 --> 00:22:40.500
When you're lost and alone, call out and lead me to your side

311
00:22:40.720 --> 00:22:45.920
As you wander far from home, you search the sky and never hide

312
00:22:45.920 --> 00:22:48.720
You are so much like the moon

313
00:22:48.720 --> 00:22:53.370
Calmer than a star, your twinkling's lost

314
00:22:56.820 --> 00:23:05.770
A deep reflection shines, you slowly leave, fading, and what's the cost?

315
00:23:05.830 --> 00:23:11.000
Stay as you are, don't lose your way

316
00:23:11.000 --> 00:23:19.310
Let my words guide you, and look ahead until the day!

317
00:23:19.950 --> 00:23:26.200
Don't give up on your dreams, through endless nights they come to you

318
00:23:26.200 --> 00:23:31.820
If you stop, you'll never see them shining through!

319
00:23:33.060 --> 00:23:37.590
Will you return? Maybe not... Will you learn? I hope you do

320
00:23:37.590 --> 00:23:43.980
Please put your past to rest, and live your life anew.
